<dl id="n36193c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36193c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36193c"> 193(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ten petticoats</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Their <mark>petticoats</mark> of linsey-woolsey were striped with a variety of gorgeous dyes&mdash;though I must confess these gallant garments were rather short, scarce reaching below the knee; but then they <mark>made up in the number</mark>, which generally equalled that of a gentleman&apos;s small clothes. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 103</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
